    <stitle>HENDRICKSON SUSPENSION SYSTEMS - ASSEMBLE - RS SERIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>RS SERIES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Saddles</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply rust preventative to the cleaned vertical drive pin bushings. Assemble the
                    bushings into the bores.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The bushings are not "press fit"; they should slide easily into the saddle bores.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the vertical drive bushing caps and locknuts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300639">Figure 39</hotlnk>). Tighten the locknuts evenly to the value found in the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0300639" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0300639" filename="../figg03/G0300639.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 39. Saddles</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1.SADDLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2.VERTICAL BUSHING RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>3.VERTICAL BUSHING RETAINER NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>4.VERTICAL BUSHING RETAINER STUD</callout1>
                        <callout1>5.VERTICAL PIN BUSHING NUT</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Frame Brackets</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new, or removed and inspected frame brackets to the frame rails (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300640">Figure 40</hotlnk>). Tighten the fasteners to the values found in the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0300640" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0300640" filename="../figg03/G0300640.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 40. Vertical Drive Pin Locknuts</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1.FULL LENGTH SPACER (THICKNESS MUST EQUAL THE GAP BETWEEN THE BRACKET FLANGE AND THE
                            FRAME LINER)
                        </callout1>
                        <callout1>2.VERTICAL DRIVE PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>3.WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4.LOCK NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5.MINIMUM OF (2) FULL THREADS MUST EXTEND BEYOND THE END OF THE NUT AFTER TIGHTENING
                            TO THE VALUE FOUND IN THE TORQUE CHART
                        </callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a full-length spacer between the horizontal flange holes and the underside of
                    the frame reinforcing liner (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300640">Figure 40</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The brackets are to fit tightly and flush against the bottom of the main frame rail when
                    the fasteners are installed (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300641">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0300641" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0300641" filename="../figg03/G0300641.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 41. Frame Brackets</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1.FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                        <callout1>2.CROSSMEMBER GUSSET</callout1>
                        <callout1>3.HARDENED FLAT-WASHER (BOTH SIDES)</callout1>
                        <callout1>4.GRADE C LOCKNUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5.FULL LENGTH SPACER</callout1>
                        <callout1>6.ALL BOLTS TO BE GRADE 8</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Within this area, the horizontal flange of the frame bracket must fit flush and tight
                            against the bottom horizontal flange of the frame rail.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Saddle Assemblies and Cushions</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Coat the frame bracket vertical drive pins and the vertical drive bushing I.D.s with a
                    rust preventative. Position the load cushions on the saddles, then raise the saddles, guiding the
                    vertical drive bushings over the frame bracket pins.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the drive pin washers over the threaded ends of the drive pins with the concave
                    washer lips pointing downward.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If washers are installed incorrectly with the lips pointing upward, the washer lips will
                            cut into the rubber of the vertical drive bushings and restrict the normal movement of the
                            bushings. This can affect ride characteristics. Properly installed washers allow the correct
                            upward motion of the vertical drive bushings.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the vertical drive pin locknuts (refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300640">Figure 40</hotlnk>) and tighten to the values found in the
                    <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>When the locknuts are tightened correctly, the ends of the vertical drive bushing inner
                            metals are clamped securely between the shoulders of the frame brackets and the concave
                            washers.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>All motion will be accommodated by rubber deflection, and there will be no movement
                            between mating metal surfaces.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Standard vertical drive pin locknuts are not used on vehicles that will have the rebound
                            control stop installed.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Rebound Control Stop Kit</title>
            <para>Assemble the special stop nuts and bumpers with the existing concave washers in the original
                positions. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300642">Figure 42</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300642" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300642" filename="../figg03/G0300642.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Rebound Control Stop Kit</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.SADDLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.VERTICAL DRIVE BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.VERTICAL DRIVE PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.CONCAVE WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.BUMPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.VERTICAL DRIVE BUSHING CAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.STOP NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
